import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased persons?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(gender_counts.index, gender_counts.values, color=['blue', 'red'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Gender')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased persons?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    race_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['red', 'blue', 'green', 'orange'])
    plt.title('What is the race distribution of the deceased persons?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Race')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('type').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 3), subplot_kw=dict(aspect="equal"))
    wedges, texts, autotexts = ax.pie(data['counts'], autopct='%1.1f%%', textprops=dict(color="w"))
    ax.legend(wedges, data['type'], title="Type of Event", loc="center left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    plt.setp(autotexts, size=10, weight="bold")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of the type of event that led to the death of the deceased persons?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of the locations where the deceased persons were killed?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
